e timeout, the Captain or Designated Alternate from either team does. \r\n\r\nRDRotD',3),(67,'71.23.91.114',1335445181,640,0,'Question #640: I\\\'m reporting question #640 because ... \r\n\r\nThis rule should read:\r\n\r\n“... and re-enters the track in front of one *pack* skater”. This is …”\r\n\r\n6.13.11 - A skater, after addressing mid jam equipment malfunction, re-entering the track in front of one pack skater.\r\n\r\nAfter all, there is no penalty for returning from addressing an equipment malfunction in front of either or both Jammers. \r\n\r\nRDRotD',3),(68,'63.246.173.134',1335445216,316,0,'Question #316: I\\\'m reporting question #316 because ... I read that as the first set of four whistles, which would make the answer true, but since the correct answer is false, I assume you meant the first whistle blast of four.  Therefore, i think you should clarify the question to say first whistle blast of four to make it clearer.',3),(69,'71.23.91.114',1335445493,381,0,'Question #381: I\\\'m reporting question #381 because ... \r\n\r\nAlthough I understand the intent of this question, I don’t particularly agree with its wording. Technically, a skater gets a major penalty for habitually falling small in front of opponents after the third time. Meaning, she falls small a third time, and after it has happened the penalty is issued. So going by actual course of action, a skater can fall small three times before getting a major penalty for it, not twice. They can do so twice without getting a penalty at all, and then after the third time they get the penalty\r\n\r\nRDRotD',2),(70,'71.23.91.114',1335469365,54,0,'Question #54: I\\\'m reporting question #54 because ... Seems piddly but I would change \\\"period timer\\\" to \\\"official period clock\\\".\r\n\r\nRDRotD',3),(71,'71.23.91.114',1335469472,717,0,'Question #717: I\\\'m reporting question #717 because ... Nothing wrong with the question, but the Q says \\\"penalized\\\" but the answers all say \\\"penalised\\\".\r