 landing\\\' The correct answer is now B',2),(777,'173.252.49.68',1392860093,191,0,'Question #191: I\\\'m reporting question #191 because ... I think its wrong doesn\\\'t match the rule ',1),(778,'121.45.169.153',1392866069,451,0,'Question #451: I\\\'m reporting question #451 because ... \\\"neither\\\" indicates a choice of two items. Grammatically option D is awkward.',3),(779,'86.29.15.179',1392910907,996,0,'Question #996: I\\\'m reporting question #996 because ... \r\n\r\nAt a minimum protective gear shall include:\r\n\r\nthe answer \\\'B. Mouth Guards\\\' seems incomplete, rule 10.1.2 = \\\"10.1.2 - Protective gear shall include, at a minimum: wrist guards, elbow pads, knee pads, mouth guards, and helmets.\\\" ',3),(780,'50.240.172.81',1392926304,1161,0,'Question #1161: I\\\'m reporting question #1161 because ... \r\n\r\n\r\n6.3.6 - Any contact outside of the normal skating motion which lands below the legal target zone and causes an opposing skater to fall or lose relative position.\r\n \r\n\r\n6.3.7 - Any contact outside of the normal skating motion initiated with a part of the body below the legal blocking zone that causes an opposing skater to fall or lose relative position.\r\n\r\nThe answer should be false, since it says \\\"ANY\\\" contact which would also refer to and include the \\\"normal skating motion\\\".\r\n\r\nThanks for this site!  It totally rocks!',3),(781,'86.147.19.102',1392931222,1538,0,'Question #1538: I\\\'m reporting question #1538 because ... Testing reportsd',4),(782,'68.97.169.109',1392950128,1693,0,'Question #1693: I\\\'m reporting question #1693 because ... \r\n\r\nOnly out of play penalties for failure to reform and failure to return require a warning before being issued a penalty. ',2),(783,'134.179.104.127',1392989456,1616,0,'Question #1616: I\\\'m reporting question #1616 because ... grammer.\r\n\r\n\\\'. . . 30 seconds of fewer . . .\\\' should read \\\' . . . 30 seconds or fewer . . .\\\'',2),(784,'98.245.209.214',1393017273,1